.TH lineSelect  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBlineSelect\fR \-  Selects all objects that fall across the specified line coordinates
.SH Syntax \fBlineSelect\fR  [-help]   <mode>   <ux1> <uy1> <ux2> <uy2> 
.P Selects all objects that fall across the specified line coordinates. The lineSelect command is equivalent to the Select by Line check box in the Selection page of the Preferences form.
.P Innovus provides an easy way to toggle between window and line selection modes using the GUI:
.RS  "*" 2 The default selection mode is window.  "*" 2 Press the Ctrl key to switch to the line selection mode. With the Ctrl key pressed, draw a line across the objects you want to select. All the objects that the line crosses are selected.  "*" 2 When you release the Ctrl key, the selection mode switches back to window.
.RE
.P Note: This command works only in GUI mode. 
.SH Parameters   "\fB-help\fR" Prints a brief description that includes type and default information for each lineSelect parameter.  For a detailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use the man command:   man lineSelect  "\fB<mode>\fR" Specifies the action to be performed on the objects falling across the specified line coordinates. Choose one of the following modes:
.RS  "*" 2 new: Selects all objects crossed by the line. This mode is equivalent to the Select by Line check box in the Selection page of the Preferences form.  "*" 2 delete: Deletes all object selections crossed by the line. Use this mode if multiple objects are selected and you want to deselect some of them but retain the other selections.  "*" 2 append: Selects objects crossed by the line and appends them to the current selection.  "*" 2 toggle: Deselects objects in the bounding box if they are selected; selects objects if they are deselected.
.RE   "\fB<ux1 uy1 ux2 uy2>\fR" Specifies the start and end points of the line. 
.SH Example
.P The following command selects all objects falling across the specified line coordinates.
.P lineSelect new 168.654 994.049 688.129 436.224 
.SH Related Information
.RS  "*" 2 windowSelect  "*" 2 windowToggleSelect
.RE
.P
